11/04/2010
WARSAW, Poland -- Balkan leaders expressed their condolences to Poland on Saturday (April 10th) after the tragic death of Polish President Lech Kaczynski and other top officials.
Kaczynski died in a plane crash in western Russia on Saturday along with a group of the country's political, military and religious elite.
The Polish delegation was travelling to Russia to attend the 70th anniversary of the massacre of more than 20,000 Polish military officers by Soviet secret police in the Katyn Forest.
All 96 passengers were killed as their plane crashed near the Smolensk Air Base amid thick fog.
Poland has announced a week of national mourning.
(BTA, ANA-MPA, Anadolu news agency, Mediafax, Beta, MIA - 10/04/10)
